    "body": "Problem:  When Nvim exits while connecting to a socket it leads to\n          stack-buffer-overflow.\nSolution: Associate the handle with the Stream and use the Stream's\n          internal_close_cb to update the \"closed\" status.\n",
    "closed_at": "2026-04-25T12:07:22Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> The handle being closed there is the watcher->uv.pipe.handle (the initial probe connection before the real connection is established), so it doesn't have a Stream associated with it.\r\n\r\nThat's not the probe connection. In fact it's not a connection at all. It's the \"server\", although it's not referred to as such in this source file. I'll just change the function name to `early_server_close_cb()`.",
            "created_at": "2026-04-25T01:36:14Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/39387#issuecomment-4317411183",
